summary: SummaryIT Cosmetics CC+ Cream with SPF 50+ goes beyond color-correcting to include your full coverage foundation, anti-aging serum and broad-spectrum sunscreen in one.
details: DetailsBenefitsThe #1 SPF Foundation in America*, CC+ Cream provides all-in-one complexion perfection with a natural finish.The deepest shades are formulated with broad-spectrum clear SPF so there is no white cast left on skin after application.98% said product instantly conceals the appearance of acne marks/scars**90% said product instantly conceals the appearance of dark spots**90% said product feels lightweight^Up to 24-hour wear93% said product makes skin feel moisturized^*Source: Circana/ U.S. Prestige Beauty Total Measured Market, Makeup Sales, SPF Attribute, 12 Months ending December 2023**Based on consumer perception results with makeup on.^Based on consumer perception results after one week of use.FeaturesFull-coverage foundationBroad-spectrum SPF 50+Instantly camouflages the look of top skin concerns, including:Redness on skinAcne scars/marksUneven skin toneDark spotsKey IngredientsHyaluronic Acid: Helps hydrate, visibly plump and minimize the look of fine lines & wrinklesVitamin E: Helps soothe and nourish skinNiacinamide: Helps minimize the look of discoloration & promotes even-toned, radiant skinSPF 50+: Provides broad-spectrum sun protectionItem 2264064How To UseApply 1-2 pumps of CC+ Cream with SPF 50+ to clean skin using your favorite IT Cosmetics makeup brush. Can be used as your moisturizer, anti-aging serum, concealer, foundation and sunscreen, based on your coverage needs.For best results, apply a smooth, even layer to your face, neck, and décolleté for complexion perfection.Beauty tip: Focus on parts of your face that may need the most coverage first, such as under your eyes, around your nose and mouth, chin and center of forehead - all of which typically require color correction for acne or uneven skin tone.IngredientsActive Ingredients: Titanium Dioxide 9.02%, Zinc Oxide 6.3%. reviews.headline: IT Cosmetics scores again with this one!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I don't usually gravitate towards a full coverage finish these days as my skin matures, but this full coverage CC cream works so well on my combo skin I find myself continually reaching for it. I love that it's not as heavy feeling on your skin as other full coverage foundations (however this stuff is THICK), and it is perfectly mattifying without giving an overly dry finished look. I do find because the product itself is so thick (and because of the SPF added), it can be more difficult to blend out. A flat top foundation brush, followed by a damp beauty blender (and a little more elbow grease and time than I usually prefer), and it was blended to perfection. The miracle in this product, and what's so important with my combo skin that leans more on the oily side is that even after a full day, my skin was still matte!

faceoff_positive.comments:
I ordered the cc cream because it had more shades than the Bye Bye Foundation and it had travel size so I could try the different shades to try to get a closer match to my skin color than I did when I tried 2 different Bye Bye Foundations.

I really like this CC cream. It is a bit lighter than the Bye Bye Foundation in weight. Goes on smoothly and moisturizes my skin well. I have dryer skin especially around the eyes. Good coverage but I do wear the bye bye concealer with it. Gives your skin a dewy appearance which I like. Does not go into lines, same as the Bye Bye Foundation and SPF 50. If I want a more air brushed finish I use the powdered Bye Bye Foundation I purchased on QVC. It is SPF50 on its own, but when I use it alone I do not get the hormonal age spot coverage and my face looks dusty so I use it with either the foundation or the CC cream for perfect finish.

I really like it. I purchased 2 travel tubes different shades. First one seems perfect. Will purchase again and will probably stick with the travel size to keep it fresh :)
faceoff_positive.headline: Very pleased

faceoff_negative.comments: After watching rave reviews of this CC cream from some of my favorite YouTubers, I had some extremely high expectations for this product that were sadly not met. I have 40 year old, normal/slight combination skin with occasional dry patches. This cream would cling to my dry patches, oxidize leaving me with an orange hue after a few hours, and separate on top of my slightly oily T-zone. I tried applying this product with and without primer, with a foundation brush, with a beauty blender, with just with my fingers and then I gave up. I passed it on to my 65 year old mother who turned right around and gave it back to me saying that it overly emphasized her wrinkles by settling in them over time, and that it made the rest of her face look like an oil slick. -- My biggest regret is that I used up so much of this cream trying to make it work that I cannot in good conscience return it for a refund.
